        "## 4. Fetch Seasonal Climate Data from Open-Meteo\n",
        "\n",
        "**Why:** Yield depends on climate during the growing season.\n",
        "A wheat year with low rainfall and high temperatures will have lower yield.\n",
        "We need to capture this with real seasonal climate aggregates.\n",
        "\n",
        "**How:** We call the Open-Meteo Historical API for Tunisia (lat=34.0, lon=9.0 — central Tunisia).\n",
        "For each crop group × year, we fetch daily weather for the correct season window,\n",
        "then compute seasonal aggregates:\n",
        "\n",
        "| Feature | Description |\n",
        "|---------|-------------|\n",
        "| `precip_total_mm` | Total precipitation during season |\n",
        "| `temp_mean_c` | Mean daily temperature |\n",
        "| `temp_max_c` | Mean of daily max temperatures (heat stress) |\n",
        "| `et0_total_mm` | Total reference evapotranspiration |\n",
        "| `rh_mean_pct` | Mean relative humidity |\n",
        "| `wind_mean_kmh` | Mean wind speed |\n",
        "| `dry_days` | Days with precipitation < 1mm (drought indicator) |\n",
        "| `hot_days` | Days with temp > 35°C (heat stress indicator) |\n",
        "\n",
        "> ⏱️ This step makes ~25 API calls (one per year). It takes about 2–3 minutes.\n",
        "> A progress bar will show you the status."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "CQ-OBkBqvsu3"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# ── Tunisia coordinates (central) ─────────────────────────────────────────\n",
        "LAT = 34.0\n",
        "LON = 9.0\n",
        "\n",
        "def fetch_season_climate(year, start_month, end_month):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Fetch daily climate data for Tunisia for a specific season window.\n",
        "\n",
        "    Handles cross-year seasons (e.g., winter cereals: Nov year → Jun year+1)\n",
        "    by fetching Nov–Dec of current year + Jan–Jun of next year.\n",
        "\n",
        "    Returns a dict of seasonal aggregate features.\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    # Build date range\n",
        "    if start_month <= end_month:\n",
        "        # Same year season (e.g., Mar–Sep)\n",
        "        date_from = f\"{year}-{start_month:02d}-01\"\n",
        "        # Last day of end_month\n",
        "        import calendar\n",
        "        last_day = calendar.monthrange(year, end_month)[1]\n",
        "        date_to   = f\"{year}-{end_month:02d}-{last_day}\"\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        # Cross-year season (e.g., Nov–Jun: Nov/Dec of year, Jan–Jun of year+1)\n",
        "        import calendar\n",
        "        date_from = f\"{year}-{start_month:02d}-01\"\n",
        "        last_day  = calendar.monthrange(year + 1, end_month)[1]\n",
        "        date_to   = f\"{year + 1}-{end_month:02d}-{last_day}\"\n",
        "\n",
        "    url = (\n",
        "        \"https://archive-api.open-meteo.com/v1/archive\"\n",
        "        f\"?latitude={LAT}&longitude={LON}\"\n",
        "        f\"&start_date={date_from}&end_date={date_to}\"\n",
        "        \"&daily=precipitation_sum,temperature_2m_mean,temperature_2m_max,\"\n",
        "        \"et0_fao_evapotranspiration,relative_humidity_2m_mean,wind_speed_10m_mean\"\n",
        "        \"&timezone=Africa%2FTunis\"\n",
        "    )\n",
        "\n",
        "    try:\n",
        "        resp = requests.get(url, timeout=30)\n",
        "        resp.raise_for_status()\n",
        "        data = resp.json()[\"daily\"]\n",
        "\n",
        "        precip  = [v for v in data[\"precipitation_sum\"]             if v is not None]\n",
        "        temp    = [v for v in data[\"temperature_2m_mean\"]           if v is not None]\n",
        "        tmax    = [v for v in data[\"temperature_2m_max\"]            if v is not None]\n",
        "        et0     = [v for v in data[\"et0_fao_evapotranspiration\"]    if v is not None]\n",
        "        rh      = [v for v in data[\"relative_humidity_2m_mean\"]     if v is not None]\n",
        "        wind    = [v for v in data[\"wind_speed_10m_mean\"]           if v is not None]\n",
        "\n",
        "        return {\n",
        "            \"precip_total_mm\" : round(sum(precip), 2),\n",
        "            \"temp_mean_c\"     : round(np.mean(temp), 3)  if temp else None,\n",
        "            \"temp_max_c\"      : round(np.mean(tmax), 3)  if tmax else None,\n",
        "            \"et0_total_mm\"    : round(sum(et0), 2),\n",
        "            \"rh_mean_pct\"     : round(np.mean(rh), 3)    if rh   else None,\n",
        "            \"wind_mean_kmh\"   : round(np.mean(wind), 3)  if wind else None,\n",
        "            \"dry_days\"        : sum(1 for p in precip if p < 1.0),\n",
        "            \"hot_days\"        : sum(1 for t in tmax if t > 35.0),\n",
        "            \"season_days\"     : len(precip),\n",
        "        }\n",
        "\n",
        "    except Exception as e:\n",
        "        print(f\"    ⚠️  API error for {year} ({date_from}→{date_to}): {e}\")\n",
        "        return None\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"✅ fetch_season_climate() function defined\")\n",
        "print(\"   Ready to fetch data in next cell.\")"
      ],
