        "## 5. Merge Yield Data with Climate Features\n",
        "\n",
        "Now we join the two datasets on `(crop_group, year)`.\n",
        "\n",
        "Every crop row gets the seasonal climate features for its group and year.\n",
        "For example:\n",
        "- Wheat 2010 → gets Nov 2010 – Jun 2011 climate aggregates\n",
        "- Tomatoes 2015 → gets Mar–Sep 2015 climate aggregates"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "rKmVKCCpwYz6"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# ── Merge ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
        "df_merged = df.merge(\n",
        "    df_climate,\n",
        "    on=[\"crop_group\", \"year\"],\n",
        "    how=\"left\"\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Check merge quality\n",
        "total_rows    = len(df_merged)\n",
        "matched_rows  = df_merged[\"precip_total_mm\"].notna().sum()\n",
        "unmatched     = total_rows - matched_rows\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Total rows after merge : {total_rows}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Rows with climate data : {matched_rows}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Unmatched rows         : {unmatched}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "if unmatched > 0:\n",
        "    print(\"\\n⚠️  Unmatched rows (no climate data):\")\n",
        "    print(df_merged[df_merged[\"precip_total_mm\"].isna()][[\"crop\",\"year\",\"crop_group\"]].head(10))\n",
        "\n",
