        "## 6. Feature Engineering\n",
        "\n",
        "We add a few more features that will help the regression model:\n",
        "\n",
        "| Feature | Why |\n",
        "|---------|-----|\n",
        "| `water_deficit_mm` | ET0 − Precipitation: how much water the crop needed but didn't get |\n",
        "| `year_trend` | Year centered at 2012: captures agricultural practice improvements over time |\n",
        "| `log_yield` | Log-transformed yield: stabilizes variance (yield is right-skewed) |\n",
        "| `crop_encoded` | Integer label for crop (needed for tree-based models) |\n",
        "| `group_encoded` | Integer label for crop group |\n",
        "\n",
        "We also drop columns not needed for modeling."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "N5tdqxAnwqhZ"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# ── Derived climate features ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
        "\n",
        "# Water deficit: how much evaporative demand exceeded rainfall (drought pressure)\n",
        "df_merged[\"water_deficit_mm\"] = (\n",
        "    df_merged[\"et0_total_mm\"] - df_merged[\"precip_total_mm\"]\n",
        ").round(2)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Year as a centered trend variable (helps model learn improvement over time)\n",
        "df_merged[\"year_trend\"] = df_merged[\"year\"] - 2012\n",
        "\n",
        "# Log yield (stabilises right-skewed yield distribution for regression)\n",
        "df_merged[\"log_yield\"] = np.log1p(df_merged[\"yield_kg_ha\"]).round(6)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"✅ Derived features added\")\n",
        "print(f\"   water_deficit_mm range : {df_merged['water_deficit_mm'].min():.1f} – {df_merged['water_deficit_mm'].max():.1f} mm\")\n",
        "print(f\"   year_trend range       : {df_merged['year_trend'].min()} – {df_merged['year_trend'].max()}\")\n",
        "print(f\"   log_yield range        : {df_merged['log_yield'].min():.3f} – {df_merged['log_yield'].max():.3f}\")"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
